/**
@page features Features of Gamedev Framework (gf)

Gamedev Framework (gf) is a game framework, it provides some useful features for developping 2D games. Here is a short list of some of the main features of gf:

- Core
  - Vector and matrix library
  - Geometry library
  - Noise library
  - Easings
- Window
  - Multiple monitors handling
  - Complete window events
  - Complete input events, including gamepads
  - Easy fullscreen
- Graphics
  - Views (a.k.a. cameras)
  - Sprites and animated sprites
  - Text and fonts
  - NinePatch
  - Sprite batch
  - Texture atlas
  - Tile layers
  - Post-processing effects
  - Immediate mode GUI
  - Particles
- Game
  - Resource loader
  - Application messages
  - Simple physics engine
  - Roguelike toolkit and console

If you are looking for a full game engine, you should take a look at [the list of game engines on Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_game_engines).

@sa [The Engine FAQ on /r/gamedev wiki](https://www.reddit.com/r/gamedev/wiki/engine_faq)

